definitions: To enter or operate (data or a device) by means of a keyboard or keypad.
To fasten or secure with a key.
To provide (a mechanism or system) with a key.
To adjust the pitch or tone of (a musical instrument or passage).
To scratch or damage (a car or other surface) with a key or similar object.
examples: The piano needs to be keyed.
Someone keyed my car last night.
